article.headline: Kennesaw 91, Belmont 87
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Golden Ingle scored a career-high 34 points to lead Kennesaw State to a 91-87 victory over Belmont Saturday night. The Owls (4-3, 2-0 Atlantic Sun Conference) held a six-point lead at the half and withstood the Bruins (3-2, 1-1) in the second half when Belmont cut the lead to two points twice in the first nine minutes, but never got closer than three over the final 10:41. Boomer Herndon led Belmont with 27 points. Ronnell Wooten added 26 points for the Owls, hitting 6 of 7 shots from 3-point range.
